This paper is primarily focused on applying deep reinforcement learning to real-world robotic manipulation tasks, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of soft Q-learning, which is a type of machine learning algorithm, and explores the use of energy-based models, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of policies represented by images, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the use of compositionality to create new policies, which is a concept that is relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
